        <hl1>EXECUTIVE CHANGES</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>AVADO BRANDS, Madison, Ga., named Ronald N. Magruder chief executive at its Hops Restaurant Bar Brewery brand, succeeding Tom Schelldorf, who left.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>AVADO BRANDS, Madison, Ga., named Ronald N. Magruder chief executive at its Hops Restaurant Bar Brewery brand, succeeding Tom Schelldorf, who left.</p>
        <p>CMGI VENTURES, Andover, Mass., named Jonathan D. Callaghan, a general partner, as managing partner, a post he will share with the company's co-founder, Peter Mills.</p>
        <p>H. J. HEINZ CO., Pittsburgh, named David Williams, executive vice president in charge of its Asia-Pacific and South American units, to the posts of president and chief executive at its European business. Mr. Williams succeeds Malcolm Ritchie, who is leaving.</p>
      </block>
